This paper presents a control framework for a robot's push recovery, which involves dynamic stepping properties and swing dynamics. The paper focuses on the control aspect of the robot's motion, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses a linear model and discrete LQR controllers, which are common techniques in control theory and signal processing, respectively. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also mentions using simple state estimation and basic position tracking, which suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions using inverse kinematics, which is a common technique in computer vision and graphics, suggesting that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.RO and cs.SY, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.CV.
